    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-08-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-08-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="442" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d442">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">The Marquis Montholon</persName> to
                                    <persName type="to">Mr. Hunter</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of France to the United
                                            States,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-08-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 4, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I hasten to let you know that I have
                                just received from his excellency Marshal Bazaine a despatch
                                announcing to me that the government of Mexico has decided that the
                                American materiel unduly taken over to the Mexican bank on the
                                surrender of Brownsville, to which the letter of your excellency
                                addressed to me the 12th July relates, should be restored without
                                delay to the federal authorities, and that orders were immediately
                                sent to Matamoras to assure the execution of this decision.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, the assurances of my high consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>MONTHOLON.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Hunter</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
